ActRoyal Canadian Mounted Police Act
SubjectPolicing Services in British Columbia
PrecisOrder authorizing the Minister of Public Safety and Emergency Preparedness, on behalf of the Government of Canada, to enter into an ARRANGEMENT with the Government of BRITISH COLUMBIA for the use or employment of the ROYAL CANADIAN MOUNTED POLICE, in aiding in the administration of justice at the Vancouver International Airport, and in carrying into effect the laws in force in that province.
